                <h3 class="mt-3">About BadgeBot</h3>
                <p class="text-normal text-justify pt-4">
                BadgeBot is the world's first <a href="https://www.imsglobal.org/sites/default/files/Badges/OBv2p0Final/index.html" target="_blank">Open Badges</a> issuing Twitter bot that:
                    <ul>
                        <li>uses Twitter timelines and tweets as evidence, displayer of badges, and access to badges.</li>
                        <li>saves all badge data as public gists.</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                <p>The BadgeBot code is available at <a href="https://gist.github.com/badgebotio" target="_blank" title="BadgeBot Github">https://gist.github.com/badgebotio</a> and is issued under the <a href="https://douglass.io/the-bcl" targe="_blank">BCL License</a>. All are welcomed to use and contribute.
                </p>

                <p>The initial release of this project has been supported and inspired by <a href="https://www.participate.com/" target="_blank">Participate.com</a> with some additional support from the <a href="https://opencollective.com/openrecognition" target="_blank">Open Recognition Alliance (ORA)</a>.</p>

                <p>BadgeBot is a prototype and may not be available at all times. If you are interested in supporting BadgeBot resources and/or creating a badge to be issued on BadgeBot, please DM <a href="https://twitter.com/BadgeBotio" target="_blank">@badgebotio</a> or contribute to <a href="https://opencollective.com/openrecognition" target="_blank">Open Recognition Alliance (ORA)</a>.

                <div class="smaller-text pt-3">BadgeBot graphics were created by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/danielle-chelles-17356231/" target="_blank">Danielle Chelles</a>.</div>

            </div>
